with the ocean and the idea

00:25:14.790 --> 00:25:17.670 align:middle line:84%
of the place that
we're actually in,

00:25:17.670 --> 00:25:21.700 align:middle line:84%
and sometimes we play
with those images too.

00:25:21.700 --> 00:25:27.720 align:middle line:84%
But it's perhaps more than just
the representation of place.

00:25:27.720 --> 00:25:33.570 align:middle line:84%
It's more of emergence from
the experience of being here.

00:25:33.570 --> 00:25:36.710 align:middle line:90%


00:25:36.710 --> 00:25:39.250 align:middle line:84%
>> I suppose we can say
there's more greens and blues

00:25:39.250 --> 00:25:41.620 align:middle line:84%
in our work because
of being here.

00:25:41.620 --> 00:25:43.048 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:25:43.048 --> 00:25:44.000 align:middle line:90%


00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:50.067 align:middle line:84%
What we see ourselves creating
is perhaps not as geometrical

00:25:50.067 --> 00:25:51.650 align:middle line:84%
as it might be if
we were in the city.

00:25:51.650 --> 00:25:55.420 align:middle line:90%


00:25:55.420 --> 00:25:59.590 align:middle line:84%
I think that urban living
creates particular mental sort

00:25:59.590 --> 00:26:05.790 align:middle line:84%
of metaphors and that
one tends to riff on

00:26:05.790 --> 00:26:06.900 align:middle line:90%
without even knowing it.

00:26:06.900 --> 00:26:09.430 align:middle line:90%


00:26:09.430 --> 00:26:13.530 align:middle line:84%
And I think the rural
landscape, the natural landscape

00:26:13.530 --> 00:26:15.420 align:middle line:90%
does the same thing.

00:26:15.420 --> 00:26:17.340 align:middle line:84%
>> I think we're
influenced-- you're right--

00:26:17.340 --> 00:26:23.130 align:middle line:84%
in unconscious ways about
what we are surrounded

00:26:23.130 --> 00:26:25.650 align:middle line:90%
by, the shapes and the lines.

00:26:25.650 --> 00:26:29.160 align:middle line:84%
>> Cityscapes tend to be a
lot more angular, up and down,

00:26:29.160 --> 00:26:35.820 align:middle line:84%
vertical lines,
