could've walked off

00:28:07.470 --> 00:28:09.480 align:middle line:84%
the end of the job
in Sydney onto this--

00:28:09.480 --> 00:28:10.770 align:middle line:90%
it was exactly the same.

00:28:10.770 --> 00:28:13.480 align:middle line:84%
Six lanes right
through a subdivision,

00:28:13.480 --> 00:28:14.610 align:middle line:90%
through an old suburb.

00:28:14.610 --> 00:28:19.230 align:middle line:84%
And the job sent me
out to Vancouver.

00:28:19.230 --> 00:28:21.240 align:middle line:84%
It was this time of
year, about March.

00:28:21.240 --> 00:28:24.960 align:middle line:10%
You know, it was just all gray
snow and freezing in Toronto.

00:28:24.960 --> 00:28:28.140 align:middle line:84%
And out here, it
was cherry blossoms

00:28:28.140 --> 00:28:31.620 align:middle line:84%
and pretty girls and
springs had sprung.

00:28:31.620 --> 00:28:36.610 align:middle line:84%
I just said, this is for me,
and I've been in BC ever since.

00:28:36.610 --> 00:28:41.950 align:middle line:90%


00:28:41.950 --> 00:28:44.140 align:middle line:84%
Back in the day when
I first came here,

00:28:44.140 --> 00:28:46.450 align:middle line:90%
there was only one potter.

00:28:46.450 --> 00:28:49.190 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't like there
was lots of painters

00:28:49.190 --> 00:28:50.897 align:middle line:90%
or weavers or anything.

00:28:50.897 --> 00:28:52.480 align:middle line:84%
There wasn't much
of anything, really.

00:28:52.480 --> 00:28:55.390 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't the Isle of
the Arts 40 years ago.

00:28:55.390 --> 00:28:59.470 align:middle line:84%
It was the isle of
cheap land and hippies

00:28:59.470 --> 00:29:03.070 align:middle line:84%
gone to bush and resentful
old farmers, really.

00:29:03.070 --> 00:29:06.840 align:middle line:90%


00:29:06.840 --> 00:29:10.350 align:middle line:84%
And you know, I'm saying that
even 30 years ago, I mean,

00:29:10.350 --> 00:29:13.110 align:middle line:84%
I was a working machine
really then when I was young.

00:29:13.110 --> 00:29:18.110 align:middle line:84%
And still, you
know, there wasn't

00:29:18.110 --> 00:29:22.240 align:middle line:84%
a living that was going to
pay for my kid's dental costs.

00:29:22.240 --> 00:29:25.590 align:middle line:84%
There just wasn't that
kind of living in it.

00:29:25.590 --> 00:29:29.420 align:middle line:84%
If you were happy living
in the bush, being poor,

00:29:29.420 --> 00:29:32.205 align:middle line:84%
you know, it would
support that, but it

00:29:32.205 --> 00:29:34.530 align:middle line:90%
was why I took other work.

00:29:34.530 --> 00:29:40.690 align:middle line:90%


00:29:40.690 --> 00:29:42.310 align:middle line:90%
I tell you what.

00:29:42.310 --> 00:29:45.040 align:middle line:84%
There isn't a
single pottery store

00:29:45.040 --> 00:29:49.780 align:middle line:84%
in the lower mainland or
Victoria operating now

00:29:49.780 --> 00:29:53.740 align:middle line:84%
that was operating
when I started potting.

00:29:53.740 --> 00:29:58.298 align:middle line:84%
As retail rents rose in the
Vancouver Victoria area,

00:29:58.298 --> 00:30:00.340 align:middle line:84%
you just can't get enough
dollars per square foot

00:30:00.340 --> 00:30:02.030 align:middle line:90%
on the shelves with pots.

00:30:02.030 --> 00:30:06.955 align:middle line:84%
You know, this is bulky,
heavy, and not very expensive.

00:30:06.955 --> 00:30:09.570 align:middle line:90%


00:30:09.570 --> 00:30:13.680 align:middle line:84%
I've experienced people coming
here, wanting to buy things.

00:30:13.680 --> 00:30:16.080 align:middle line:84%
But you know, well, just ship
it to me in San Francisco.

00:30:16.080 --> 00:30:20.010 align:middle line:84%
And many times, the
cost of the shipping

00:30:20.010 --> 00:30:24.240 align:middle line:84%
was more than the value
of the stuff inside.

00:30:24.240 --> 00:30:26.910 align:middle line:10%
I just finally said,
look, if you want my work,

00:30:26.910 --> 00:30:29.360 align:middle line:10%
you've got to walk up my road.

00:30:29.360 --> 00:30:30.160 align:middle line:10%
You know?

00:30:30.160 --> 00:30:34.047 align:middle line:10%
I sometimes think, oh, I wish
it was at a busy crossroads.

00:30:34.047 --> 00:30:35.630 align:middle line:84%
But on the other
hand, I don't really.

00:30:35.630 --> 00:30:36.880 align:middle line:90%
I like to live here like this.

00:30:36.880 --> 00:30:41.064 align:middle line:90%


00:30:41.064 --> 00:30:42.663 align:middle line:84%
>> We should get
the weed whacker.

00:30:42.663 --> 00:30:44.455 align:middle line:84%
>> Every year, I do
things with the school.

00:30:44.455 --> 00:30:45.255 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:30:45.255 --> 00:30:47.570 align:middle line:90%
Let's go.

00:30:47.570 --> 00:30:49.070 align:middle line:84%
>> Couldn't we
get a wheelbarrow?

00:30:49.070 --> 00:30:49.570 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yeah.

00:30:49.570 --> 00:30:50.570 align:middle line:90%
We need a wheelbarrow.

00:30:50.570 --> 00:30:52.070 align:middle line:90%
>> Go get a wheelbarrow.

00:30:52.070 --> 00:30:56.130 align:middle line:84%
>> Hundreds of kids have been
through here over the last 35

00:30:56.130 --> 00:30:57.888 align:middle line:90%
years.

00:30:57.888 --> 00:30:59.430 align:middle line:84%
It's been the
tradition at the school

00:30:59.430 --> 00:31:04.770 align:middle line:84%
