of these four-inch tiles

00:31:35.780 --> 00:31:38.360 align:middle line:84%
that we were making
the other day.

00:31:38.360 --> 00:31:40.358 align:middle line:84%
And each kid's making
it individually,

00:31:40.358 --> 00:31:42.650 align:middle line:84%
yet the whole thing's being
pulled together by the fact

00:31:42.650 --> 00:31:44.525 align:middle line:84%
that I'm just using
these two colors.

00:31:44.525 --> 00:31:46.400 align:middle line:84%
It makes sort of a
patchwork quilt out of it.

00:31:46.400 --> 00:31:58.460 align:middle line:90%


00:31:58.460 --> 00:32:01.010 align:middle line:84%
And across the board
are my dedication

00:32:01.010 --> 00:32:03.020 align:middle line:84%
to the students of
tomorrow from the students

00:32:03.020 --> 00:32:03.990 align:middle line:90%
of today sort of thing.

00:32:03.990 --> 00:32:14.540 align:middle line:90%


00:32:14.540 --> 00:32:18.470 align:middle line:10%
I love their
unfettered imagination.

00:32:18.470 --> 00:32:21.470 align:middle line:84%
It's like you look at
a little kids drawing.

00:32:21.470 --> 00:32:24.710 align:middle line:84%
They don't think about
whether, oh, I can't draw.

00:32:24.710 --> 00:32:26.060 align:middle line:90%
They just draw.

00:32:26.060 --> 00:32:28.200 align:middle line:84%
And at some point in
their development,

00:32:28.200 --> 00:32:31.010 align:middle line:84%
we become inhibited,
and then we can't draw.

00:32:31.010 --> 00:32:34.710 align:middle line:90%


00:32:34.710 --> 00:32:37.170 align:middle line:84%
Somebody who could
draw, now we can't.

00:32:37.170 --> 00:32:42.780 align:middle line:84%
And you know, I just like
to be part of getting in

00:32:42.780 --> 00:32:44.490 align:middle line:90%
before that cliff.

00:32:44.490 --> 00:32:46.335 align:middle line:90%
And you know, yes, you can.

00:32:46.335 --> 00:32:51.140 align:middle line:90%


00:32:51.140 --> 00:32:52.420 align:middle line:90%
And here's how you can.

00:32:52.420 --> 00:32:56.670 align:middle line:84%
And just the enthusiasm
of kids and their knowing

00:32:56.670 --> 00:32:57.900 align:middle line:90%
no boundaries, really.

00:32:57.900 --> 00:33:00.960 align:middle line:90%


00:33:00.960 --> 00:33:02.940 align:middle line:84%
I really, really enjoy
classes with kids.

00:33:02.940 --> 00:33:06.990 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I love the fact that a
couple of hours of pandemonium,

00:33:06.990 --> 00:33:10.110 align:middle line:84%
you know, in the end
coalesce into this table

00:33:10.110 --> 00:33:11.490 align:middle line:90%
full of quite lovely things.

00:33:11.490 --> 00:33:13.350 align:middle line:90%
And that's really fun.

00:33:13.350 --> 00:33:31.720 align:middle line:90%


00:33:31.720 --> 00:33:35.020 align:middle line:10%
>> The islands collect people
who are all interesting

00:33:35.020 --> 00:33:35.890 align:middle line:10%
in their own way.

00:33:35.890 --> 00:33:37.442 align:middle line:84%
And it's part of
the reason that we

00:33:37.442 --> 00:33:39.400 align:middle line:84%
love running the newspaper
on the Gulf Islands,

00:33:39.400 --> 00:33:41.740 align:middle line:84%
is because there's
always a story to tell.

00:33:41.740 --> 00:33:45.160 align:middle line:84%
Somebody's always doing
something really interesting

00:33:45.160 --> 00:33:47.378 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:33:47.378 --> 00:33:49.170 align:middle line:10%
It's important to look
at the buy-in local,

00:33:49.170 --> 00:33:53.100 align:middle line:10%
because you sometimes
take a little extra time

00:33:53.100 --> 00:33:55.140 align:middle line:10%
in talking to the
person who made it,

00:33:55.140 --> 00:33:57.780 align:middle line:10%
and find out whether
this is something

00:33:57.780 --> 00:34:00.242 align:middle line:10%
that's appropriate for what
you want to use it for.

00:34:00.242 --> 00:34:03.386 align:middle line:90%
And there's also that sense of--

00:34:03.386 --> 00:34:05.330 align:middle line:84%
you know, there's
the sense of pride

00:34:05.330 --> 00:34:06.950 align:middle line:84%
that it came from
your home community

00:34:06.950 --> 00:34:09.590 align:middle line:84%
rather than from
wherever in the world

00:34:09.590 --> 00:34:12.074 align:middle line:90%
it might have been made instead.

00:34:12.074 --> 00:34:13.699 align:middle line:84%
That's one of the
biggest things people

00:34:13.699 --> 00:34:15.491 align:middle line:84%
can do to make an impact
on their community

00:34:15.491 --> 00:34:19.330 align:middle line:84%
is ask that question,
can I get it locally?

00:34:19.330 --> 00:34:22.235 align:middle line:84%
I think the creativity runs
through almost anybody that

00:34:22.235 --> 00:34:24.610 align:middle line:84%
has to live on the Gulf Islands,
or chooses to live here,

00:34:24.610 --> 00:34:27.880 align:middle line:84%
because by being an
island, it forces

00:34:27.880 --> 00:34:30.340 align:middle line:84%
you to get creative in how
you do different things.

00:34:30.340 --> 00:34:33.693 align:middle line:84%
We talk about incubators in
the sense of the tech world.

00:34:33.693 --> 00:34:35.110 align:middle line:84%
For Gabriola, what
we have here is

00:34:35.110 --> 00:34:37.380 align:middle line:84%
an incubator for the creative
side, where people can

00:34:37.380 --> 00:34:41.128 align:middle line:90%
get creative about anything.

00:34:41.128 --> 00:34:43.170 align:middle line:84%
With the Isle of the Arts
Festival, they come out

00:34:43.170 --> 00:34:47.520 align:middle line:84%
and they share their techniques
and such in workshops

00:34:47.520 --> 00:34:51.989 align:middle line:84%
over the course of nine or
10 days here on Gabriola.

00:34:51.989 --> 00:34:54.330 align:middle line:90%
And locals attend those.

00:34:54.330 --> 00:34:56.130 align:middle line:90%
Visitors attend those.

00:34:56.130 --> 00:34:59.460 align:middle line:84%
The workshop hosts
themselves will often

00:34:59.460 --> 00:35:04.970 align:middle line:84%
go to other workshops and
learn new ways of doing things.

00:35:04.970 --> 00:35:08.370 align:middle line:84%
And they're showing each
other how to better do things,

00:35:08.370 --> 00:35:11.460 align:middle line:84%
how to better make things,
how to better create.

00:35:11.460 --> 00:35:29.170 align:middle line:90%


00:35:29.170 --> 00:35:34.350 align:middle line:84%
>> I try to incorporate
locally gathered materials,

00:35:34.350 --> 00:35:39.400 align:middle line:84%
just because it seems
the right thing to do.

00:35:39.400 --> 00:35:41.760 align:middle line:90%
It's more organic.

00:35:41.760 --> 00:35:45.636 align:middle line:90%
People identify with it more.

00:35:45.636 --> 00:35:48.270 align:middle line:84%
They can say, my gosh, that's
just like the blackberries

00:35:48.270 --> 00:35:51.060 align:middle line:84%
I tripped on yesterday when
I was walking on that trail.

00:35:51.060 --> 00:35:53.610 align:middle line:90%


00:35:53.610 --> 00:35:57.470 align:middle line:84%
In fact, in a lot of
cases, it's nuisance stuff.

00:35:57.470 --> 00:35:58.880 align:middle line:90%
I use ivy.

00:35:58.880 --> 00:36:01.440 align:middle line:10%
Ivy is lovely to work
with, but a lot of people

00:36:01.440 --> 00:36:03.900 align:middle line:10%
really curse it, especially
when it gets in their garden

00:36:03.900 --> 00:36:05.580 align:middle line:10%
where they don't want it.

00:36:05.580 --> 00:36:07.110 align:middle line:10%
And the blackberries
are the same.

00:36:07.110 --> 00:36:21.390 align:middle line:90%


00:36:21.390 --> 00:36:24.360 align:middle line:84%
I started making
baskets in 2002.

00:36:24.360 --> 00:36:25.980 align:middle line:10%
There was a group
of us on the island

00:36:25.980 --> 00:36:29.670 align:middle line:10%
that started by doing a
project to raise money

00:36:29.670 --> 00:36:30.700 align:middle line:10%
for the food bank.

00:36:30.700 --> 00:36:32.580 align:middle line:84%
It was about 10 of
us that were hooked.

00:36:32.580 --> 00:36:33.840 align:middle line:90%
And we kept going.

00:36:33.840 --> 00:36:35.730 align:middle line:90%
We meet every week.

00:36:35.730 --> 00:36:37.690 align:middle line:90%
We have done since then.

00:36:37.690 --> 00:36:39.900 align:middle line:84%
Meet every week in
different people's homes

00:36:39.900 --> 00:36:42.680 align:middle line:90%
and just make baskets together.

00:36:42.680 --> 00:36:45.790 align:middle line:90%


00:36:45.790 --> 00:36:49.690 align:middle line:90%
I have always loved baskets.

00:36:49.690 --> 00:36:52.930 align:middle line:84%
Right from when I was
younger, I collected them.

00:36:52.930 --> 00:36:55.375 align:middle line:90%
I bought them when I traveled.

00:36:55.375 --> 00:36:57.250 align:middle line:84%
And I always wanted to
know how to make them.

00:36:57.250 --> 00:37:01.240 align:middle line:84%
And when this opportunity came
up, it was perfect for me.

00:37:01.240 --> 00:37:10.290 align:middle line:90%


00:37:10.290 --> 00:37:13.340 align:middle line:10%
I use daffodil leaves a lot.

00:37:13.340 --> 00:37:15.200 align:middle line:10%
Make them into a cordage.

00:37:15.200 --> 00:37:18.290 align:middle line:84%
This is what you end
up with, is the cordage

00:37:18.290 --> 00:37:20.870 align:middle line:84%
that's got that lovely
golden tinge to it.

00:37:20.870 --> 00:37:32.710 align:middle line:90%


00:37:32.710 --> 00:37:39.063 align:middle line:84%
And then here, we have cedar
root and-- sorry, cedar bark.

00:37:39.063 --> 00:37:41.230 align:middle line:84%
These are pine needles that
I've gathered right here

00:37:41.230 --> 00:37:42.030 align:middle line:90%
on my street.

00:37:42.030 --> 00:37:45.490 align:middle line:90%


00:37:45.490 --> 00:37:48.580 align:middle line:84%
This is something I haven't
mentioned, deer horn.

00:37:48.580 --> 00:37:52.420 align:middle line:84%
I can drill into this
and use it for the handle

00:37:52.420 --> 00:37:55.390 align:middle line:90%
of a basket like that.

00:37:55.390 --> 00:37:58.900 align:middle line:84%
This is cedar root, which
is beautiful to work with.

00:37:58.900 --> 00:38:00.775 align:middle line:84%
When it's wet,
it's very pliable.

00:38:00.775 --> 00:38:07.950 align:middle line:90%


00:38:07.950 --> 00:38:09.690 align:middle line:90%
You have an idea, and you do it.

00:38:09.690 --> 00:38:11.140 align:middle line:90%
And if it works, it works.

00:38:11.140 --> 00:38:13.630 align:middle line:84%
If it doesn't, you do
something else with it.

00:38:13.630 --> 00:38:14.482 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:38:14.482 --> 00:38:15.282 align:middle line:90%


00:38:15.282 --> 00:38:18.750 align:middle line:84%
It's very much a
forgiving art form,

00:38:18.750 --> 00:38:24.930 align:middle line:84%
because you can shape almost
anything when it's wet.

00:38:24.930 --> 00:38:27.660 align:middle line:10%
And it dictates
its own shape too.

00:38:27.660 --> 00:38:30.960 align:middle line:84%
A lot of baskets have
a mind of their own.

00:38:30.960 --> 00:38:33.700 align:middle line:84%
And even though you're
wanting to make it this shape,

00:38:33.700 --> 00:38:38.010 align:middle line:84%
it might end up quite
different, and sometimes more

00:38:38.010 --> 00:38:39.600 align:middle line:84%
pleasant than what
you had in mind.

00:38:39.600 --> 00:38:43.920 align:middle line:90%


00:38:43.920 --> 00:38:48.360 align:middle line:84%
Often, I'm reminded of back
in the days when we first

00:38:48.360 --> 00:38:49.500 align:middle line:90%
bought our place here.

00:38:49.500 --> 00:38:54.600 align:middle line:84%
And there was a saying
that rubber gumboots

00:38:54.600 --> 00:38:58.410 align:middle line:84%
were what we all
called Gabriola dancing

00:38:58.410 --> 00:39:04.090 align:middle line:84%
shoes, because that was about as
dressed up as people got here.

00:39:04.090 --> 00:39:09.930 align:middle line:84%
So that's an aspect of this
place that we've always loved,

00:39:09.930 --> 00:39:12.840 align:middle line:90%
is that there is no pretense.

00:39:12.840 --> 00:39:16.170 align:middle line:84%
>> So how is it reflected
in your craft, in your work?

00:39:16.170 --> 00:39:19.950 align:middle line:90%


00:39:19.950 --> 00:39:23.730 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, a lot of the materials
I use are very humble.

00:39:23.730 --> 00:39:26.570 align:middle line:84%
And at the time I
started using them,

00:39:26.570 --> 00:39:30.030 align:middle line:84%
I thought, who's going to pay
money for something that you've

00:39:30.030 --> 00:39:31.980 align:middle line:84%
just gathered for nothing
out of your garden

00:39:31.980 --> 00:39:34.110 align:middle line:90%
or out of the forest?

00:39:34.110 --> 00:39:36.010 align:middle line:90%
Certainly not going to do that.

00:39:36.010 --> 00:39:38.760 align:middle line:84%
What's the point of
bothering to do that?

00:39:38.760 --> 00:39:42.310 align:middle line:84%
However, it has turned out
to be just the opposite.

00:39:42.310 --> 00:39:46.590 align:middle line:84%
People are much more
enthralled with the things

00:39:46.590 --> 00:39:51.180 align:middle line:84%
that I've made from natural,
locally gathered materials

00:39:51.180 --> 00:39:57.930 align:middle line:84%
than they are with the very
symmetrical, perfect basket

00:39:57.930 --> 00:40:02.130 align:middle line:84%
like what you can buy
in Michael's or Pier 1.

00:40:02.130 --> 00:40:07.100 align:middle line:90%


00:40:07.100 --> 00:40:13.064 align:middle line:10%
[WAVES CRASHING]

00:40:13.064 --> 00:40:42.890 align:middle line:90%


00:40:42.890 --> 00:40:46.480 align:middle line:90%
>> Saturday is the busiest day.

00:40:46.480 --> 00:40:49.490 align:middle line:84%
Well, say on a Saturday
farmer's market,

00:40:49.490 --> 00:40:53.000 align:middle line:84%
I'd sell 10 times the bread
that I would sell, say,

00:40:53.000 --> 00:40:57.050 align:middle line:90%
in a Saturday in February.

00:40:57.050 --> 00:40:58.970 align:middle line:84%
On the Saturday
market in the summer,

00:40:58.970 --> 00:41:03.890 align:middle line:84%
we'll make 11 different
kinds, I guess.

00:41:03.890 --> 00:41:05.390 align:middle line:84%
I think there's
about 11 varieties.

00:41:05.390 --> 00:41:09.220 align:middle line:90%
10, 11 varieties of scones.

00:41:09.220 --> 00:41:11.490 align:middle line:84%
And then at least 10
varieties of bread.

00:41:11.490 --> 00:41:20.256 align:middle line:90%


00:41:20.256 --> 00:41:22.290 align:middle line:90%
I pre-shape the loaves.

00:41:22.290 --> 00:41:23.340 align:middle line:90%
I shape the loaves.

00:41:23.340 --> 00:41:27.420 align:middle line:84%
I put them into the oven, and
I take them out of the oven,

00:41:27.420 --> 00:41:28.380 align:middle line:90%
and I put them in bags.

00:41:28.380 --> 00:41:33.010 align:middle line:84%
So it's touched
all the way along.

00:41:33.010 --> 00:41:38.040 align:middle line:84%
So that's a big difference,
I think, between what I do

00:41:38.040 --> 00:41:40.620 align:middle line:84%
and what a big commercial
bakery would do.

00:41:40.620 --> 00:41:45.540 align:middle line:90%


00:41:45.540 --> 00:41:50.250 align:middle line:84%
I can see how the dough's
reacting through every step

00:41:50.250 --> 00:41:53.070 align:middle line:90%
of the process.

00:41:53.070 --> 00:41:57.150 align:middle line:84%
At its worst,
commercial bread is more

00:41:57.150 --> 00:42:01.350 align:middle line:84%
like a meringue
or a marshmallow,

00:42:01.350 --> 00:42:07.770 align:middle line:84%
because it's got so many
different elements in the dough

00:42:07.770 --> 00:42:13.780 align:middle line:84%
to make it do what
time takes to do.

00:42:13.780 --> 00:42:20.790 align:middle line:84%
And so they use
conditioners and additives

00:42:20.790 --> 00:42:24.330 align:middle line:84%
to replicate this time,
because they're in a hurry.

00:42:24.330 --> 00:42:33.590 align:middle line:90%


00:42:33.590 --> 00:42:36.260 align:middle line:90%
Food for the most part is dead.

00:42:36.260 --> 00:42:37.220 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:42:37.220 --> 00:42:38.020 align:middle line:90%


00:42:38.020 --> 00:42:44.105 align:middle line:84%
You know, and I've spent 25
years putting Xs on protein.

00:42:44.105 --> 00:42:45.820 align:middle line:90%
You know, grill marks.

00:42:45.820 --> 00:42:50.210 align:middle line:84%
You know, I thought
that cooking was diverse

00:42:50.210 --> 00:42:55.410 align:middle line:84%
and that baking
would be monotonous,

00:42:55.410 --> 00:43:00.980 align:middle line:84%
but it's the complete
opposite for me.

00:43:00.980 --> 00:43:05.960 align:middle line:84%
I find even though you're doing
the same basic thing with bread

00:43:05.960 --> 00:43:13.840 align:middle line:84%
every day, there's such a
diversity and a uniqueness.

00:43:13.840 --> 00:43:14.730 align:middle line:90%
It's alive.

00:43:14.730 --> 00:43:15.772 align:middle line:90%
That's the biggest thing.

00:43:15.772 --> 00:43:19.940 align:middle line:90%


00:43:19.940 --> 00:43:22.270 align:middle line:84%
It's mentioned in a few
different books, the slow rise

00:43:22.270 --> 00:43:23.690 align:middle line:90%
method.

00:43:23.690 --> 00:43:28.235 align:middle line:84%
And so I liked that name,
because most good things

00:43:28.235 --> 00:43:29.035 align:middle line:90%
happen slowly.

00:43:29.035 --> 00:43:34.270 align:middle line:90%


00:43:34.270 --> 00:43:41.810 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't be doing this without
support from the community,

00:43:41.810 --> 00:43:45.730 align:middle line:84%
from the designer
of the building

00:43:45.730 --> 00:43:52.090 align:middle line:90%
itself who did it at no cost.

00:43:52.090 --> 00:43:54.940 align:middle line:90%


00:43:54.940 --> 00:43:57.670 align:middle line:84%
The only request
was to donate bread

00:43:57.670 --> 00:44:02.392 align:middle line:84%
to the food bank,
which I continue to do.

00:44:02.392 --> 00:44:09.200 align:middle line:84%
To residents who
lent me money to put

00:44:09.200 --> 00:44:13.640 align:middle line:84%
on a down payment for the house,
because I was self-employed

00:44:13.640 --> 00:44:18.080 align:middle line:84%
and no bank would lend
me money, to the man that

00:44:18.080 --> 00:44:23.600 align:middle line:84%
lives next door that
cleared the lot and supplied

00:44:23.600 --> 00:44:31.590 align:middle line:84%
the gravel, the sand,
who never gave me a bill.

00:44:31.590 --> 00:44:37.530 align:middle line:84%
So it's an incredible island
from that perspective.

00:44:37.530 --> 00:44:41.490 align:middle line:90%
And baking bread is a--

00:44:41.490 --> 00:44:44.090 align:middle line:90%


00:44:44.090 --> 00:44:46.160 align:middle line:84%
in hindsight, is a
very fundamental way

00:44:46.160 --> 00:44:47.520 align:middle line:90%
to give back to the community.

00:44:47.520 --> 00:44:48.320 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:44:48.320 --> 00:44:53.030 align:middle line:84%
I've never had a
job or done anything

00:44:53.030 --> 00:44:58.767 align:middle line:84%
where people thank you on a
weekly basis, if not more,

00:44:58.767 --> 00:44:59.600 align:middle line:90%
for doing what I do.

00:44:59.600 --> 00:45:03.190 align:middle line:90%


00:45:03.190 --> 00:45:05.440 align:middle line:84%
We were talking about the
industrialization of things,

00:45:05.440 --> 00:45:10.800 align:middle line:84%
and that certainly, I
think, was the downfall

00:45:10.800 --> 00:45:11.970 align:middle line:90%
of a lot of things.

00:45:11.970 --> 00:45:19.570 align:middle line:84%
And bread as a utilitarian
or as a utility that

00:45:19.570 --> 00:45:24.970 align:middle line:84%
is square and fits a toaster and
toasts quickly and efficiently

00:45:24.970 --> 00:45:36.050 align:middle line:84%
is become the norm for so many
people that outside that box,

00:45:36.050 --> 00:45:37.750 align:middle line:90%
it's foreign.

00:45:37.750 --> 00:45:41.840 align:middle line:84%
Like, the idea of having to cut
bread as opposed to having it

00:45:41.840 --> 00:45:42.720 align:middle line:90%
pre-sliced.

00:45:42.720 --> 00:45:45.750 align:middle line:90%


00:45:45.750 --> 00:45:47.818 align:middle line:84%
It takes away a
certain connection

00:45:47.818 --> 00:45:49.110 align:middle line:90%
with the product that you have.

00:45:49.110 --> 00:45:52.200 align:middle line:90%


00:45:52.200 --> 00:45:57.000 align:middle line:84%
I can't imagine
many people taking

00:45:57.000 --> 00:46:01.440 align:middle line:84%
a loaf of store-bought,
pre-sliced, square bread

00:46:01.440 --> 00:46:03.450 align:middle line:90%
and smelling it.

00:46:03.450 --> 00:46:08.433 align:middle line:84%
Whereas if you take the loaf of
bread that's been handmade out

00:46:08.433 --> 00:46:11.100 align:middle line:84%
of the bag and you've got to cut
it, you first have to touch it.

00:46:11.100 --> 00:46:13.515 align:middle line:84%
And you probably
look at the loaf.

00:46:13.515 --> 00:46:15.178 align:middle line:84%
You know, there's
a deeper connection

00:46:15.178 --> 00:46:16.470 align:middle line:90%
that you have with the product.

00:46:16.470 --> 00:46:23.302 align:middle line:90%


00:46:23.302 --> 00:46:26.110 align:middle line:84%
You know, I often use the term
that I earn a lifestyle, not

00:46:26.110 --> 00:46:28.400 align:middle line:90%
a living.

00:46:28.400 --> 00:46:31.540 align:middle line:84%
You're not going to get
very wealthy doing this,

00:46:31.540 --> 00:46:36.295 align:middle line:84%
so you earn the ability to
have a wonderful lifestyle

00:46:36.295 --> 00:46:37.526 align:middle line:90%
here on the island.

00:46:37.526 --> 00:46:45.340 align:middle line:90%


00:46:45.340 --> 00:46:50.890 align:middle line:10%
>> We have a Saturday morning
market from June through till

00:46:50.890 --> 00:46:53.350 align:middle line:10%
October.

00:46:53.350 --> 00:46:56.650 align:middle line:10%
Everything that is sold
here, all the vendors

00:46:56.650 --> 00:47:00.520 align:middle line:10%
are citizens of Gabriola
or [? Mag ?] Islands.

00:47:00.520 --> 00:47:03.310 align:middle line:10%
So everything has to be
made or produced here.

00:47:03.310 --> 00:47:06.140 align:middle line:90%


00:47:06.140 --> 00:47:10.310 align:middle line:84%
>> Made on Gabriola, it's
a very West Coast feel.

00:47:10.310 --> 00:47:16.100 align:middle line:84%
There are apparently
more artists and artisans

00:47:16.100 --> 00:47:18.170 align:middle line:84%
working and making
a living on Gabriola

00:47:18.170 --> 00:47:20.291 align:middle line:90%
than anywhere else in Canada.

00:47:20.291 --> 00:47:21.614 align:middle line:90%
>> Good morning.

00:47:21.614 --> 00:47:22.940 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:47:22.940 --> 00:47:30.290 align:middle line:84%
>> Gabriola just encourages or
attracts very creative people.

00:47:30.290 --> 00:47:32.960 align:middle line:84%
If you have a
group of something,

00:47:32.960 --> 00:47:36.080 align:middle line:84%
of people doing their
best kind of work,

00:47:36.080 --> 00:47:40.490 align:middle line:84%
it attracts other people to come
and do their best kind of work.

00:47:40.490 --> 00:47:42.200 align:middle line:90%
So you get that--

00:47:42.200 --> 00:47:43.680 align:middle line:90%
we feed off each other.

00:47:43.680 --> 00:47:46.160 align:middle line:84%
We get encouragement
from each other.

00:47:46.160 --> 00:47:50.122 align:middle line:10%
People buy our goods.

00:47:50.122 --> 00:47:51.580 align:middle line:10%
One of the things
that I've noticed

00:47:51.580 --> 00:47:54.820 align:middle line:10%
since I've been doing
this is I still sell

00:47:54.820 --> 00:47:57.550 align:middle line:10%
more every week to
the locals than I

00:47:57.550 --> 00:48:02.930 align:middle line:10%
do to the tourists, which
constantly astonishes me.

00:48:02.930 --> 00:48:07.410 align:middle line:84%
You know, the market
fulfills a big place socially

00:48:07.410 --> 00:48:08.210 align:middle line:90%
on the island.

00:48:08.210 --> 00:48:14.150 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:48:14.150 --> 00:48:33.980 align:middle line:90%


00:48:33.980 --> 00:48:40.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Now the beauty of this is it
gives me a lot of force to put

00:48:40.060 --> 00:48:43.780 align:middle line:84%
these in place
here, these screws.

00:48:43.780 --> 00:48:48.580 align:middle line:84%
And the reason I'm using this
over, say, a cordless drill

00:48:48.580 --> 00:48:52.960 align:middle line:90%
is because I want to hear.

00:48:52.960 --> 00:48:56.860 align:middle line:10%
I want to feel the tension
that I'm applying to that screw

00:48:56.860 --> 00:48:58.720 align:middle line:10%
so that I'm not
breaking anything.

00:48:58.720 --> 00:49:02.020 align:middle line:84%
But I also want to hear
if I'm cracking anything

00:49:02.020 --> 00:49:07.060 align:middle line:84%
or if anything's making an
unusual noise that does not--

00:49:07.060 --> 00:49:12.380 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't sound good, and I'm
going to have to repair later.

00:49:12.380 --> 00:49:17.510 align:middle line:84%
It's such an old-school
tool that is so functional

00:49:17.510 --> 00:49:19.440 align:middle line:84%
and still has its
place that people

00:49:19.440 --> 00:49:21.083 align:middle line:90%
don't appreciate anymore.

00:49:21.083 --> 00:49:28.440 align:middle line:90%


00:49:28.440 --> 00:49:33.850 align:middle line:84%
It's a little sail rowboat
that somebody brought to me.

00:49:33.850 --> 00:49:39.400 align:middle line:84%
His son built this boat down at
the Port Townsend boat building

00:49:39.400 --> 00:49:40.690 align:middle line:90%
school.

00:49:40.690 --> 00:49:47.370 align:middle line:84%
And his son unfortunately
had passed away way

00:49:47.370 --> 00:49:49.140 align:middle line:90%
before his time.

00:49:49.140 --> 00:49:53.390 align:middle line:84%
And so the man who
brought this to me

00:49:53.390 --> 00:49:58.090 align:middle line:84%
has asked me to restore it
for him in memory of his son.

00:49:58.090 --> 00:50:04.450 align:middle line:90%


00:50:04.450 --> 00:50:06.620 align:middle line:84%
I was painting and doing
artwork at the same time,

00:50:06.620 --> 00:50:07.578 align:middle line:90%
and I was on the fence.

00:50:07.578 --> 00:50:11.630 align:middle line:84%
I really wanted to do that
more than the boat building.

00:50:11.630 --> 00:50:14.620 align:middle line:90%
But then I got into doing--

00:50:14.620 --> 00:50:16.840 align:middle line:84%
I started getting into more
of the wood side of it,

00:50:16.840 --> 00:50:20.532 align:middle line:84%
and I really saw the
creative components to it.

00:50:20.532 --> 00:50:22.615 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's like a
three-dimensional sculpture,

00:50:22.615 --> 00:50:26.900 align:middle line:90%
a functional piece of sculpture.

00:50:26.900 --> 00:50:28.750 align:middle line:84%
And I started seeing
that side of it.

00:50:28.750 --> 00:50:31.060 align:middle line:84%
And that really changed
my point of view about it,

00:50:31.060 --> 00:50:33.230 align:middle line:84%
and it wasn't just
a job anymore.

00:50:33.230 --> 00:50:36.520 align:middle line:84%
I started seeing it
as a romantic world,

00:50:36.520 --> 00:50:37.920 align:middle line:90%
and really appreciating it.

00:50:37.920 --> 00:50:48.910 align:middle line:90%


00:50:48.910 --> 00:50:51.400 align:middle line:84%
Wooden boats, if
you maintain them,

00:50:51.400 --> 00:50:54.310 align:middle line:84%
they'll stay true and
strong for a long time.

00:50:54.310 --> 00:50:58.540 align:middle line:84%
But if you let them
drop for a year or two,

00:50:58.540 --> 00:51:00.340 align:middle line:84%
they fall very
quickly, and then they

00:51:00.340 --> 00:51:02.830 align:middle line:90%
fall into disrepair very fast.

00:51:02.830 --> 00:51:06.590 align:middle line:84%
And then to hire somebody to
fix it is quite expensive,

00:51:06.590 --> 00:51:09.760 align:middle line:84%
so that's where I
come in, is I can

00:51:09.760 --> 00:51:11.667 align:middle line:90%
teach those guys how to do it.

00:51:11.667 --> 00:51:16.810 align:middle line:90%


00:51:16.810 --> 00:51:19.960 align:middle line:84%
I've started running some
classes through my school now.

00:51:19.960 --> 00:51:25.890 align:middle line:84%
So they're woodworking classes
with a marine slant to them.

00:51:25.890 --> 00:51:29.055 align:middle line:84%
So some of them are basic
introduction to woodworking,

00:51:29.055 --> 00:51:31.430 align:middle line:84%
and then I'll teach other
things like block making, block

00:51:31.430 --> 00:51:34.250 align:middle line:90%
and pulleys.

00:51:34.250 --> 00:51:37.490 align:middle line:84%
But I'm also doing other stuff
that's fun for me as well,

00:51:37.490 --> 00:51:39.410 align:middle line:84%
and that's like driftwood
furniture making.

00:51:39.410 --> 00:51:41.548 align:middle line:84%
So we can go to
the local beaches,

00:51:41.548 --> 00:51:43.340 align:middle line:84%
and we can collect
driftwood off the beach.

00:51:43.340 --> 00:51:44.680 align:middle line:90%
And it's just this--

00:51:44.680 --> 00:51:47.780 align:middle line:84%
you know, we call it the
beach depot where we can just

00:51:47.780 --> 00:51:52.788 align:middle line:84%
go pull this beautiful material
up and build simple furniture.

00:51:52.788 --> 00:52:04.020 align:middle line:90%


00:52:04.020 --> 00:52:06.590 align:middle line:84%
I have a friend on the island
here who mills up wood.

00:52:06.590 --> 00:52:09.870 align:middle line:84%
And so I go buy a lot
of my wood from him,

00:52:09.870 --> 00:52:13.790 align:middle line:84%
and he's providing me
wood that's from Gabriola.

00:52:13.790 --> 00:52:16.020 align:middle line:84%
And then I turn around and
make things out of that.

00:52:16.020 --> 00:52:18.960 align:middle line:84%
But where would I find that
anywhere else, you know?

00:52:18.960 --> 00:52:21.580 align:middle line:84%
And be able to have the luxury
of going there and picking that

00:52:21.580 --> 00:52:25.170 align:middle line:84%
out instead of having the next
guy behind me trying to outbid

00:52:25.170 --> 00:52:28.240 align:middle line:84%
me or, you know,
trying to buy it all

00:52:28.240 --> 00:52:32.430 align:middle line:84%
because he just wants to
hoard it away somewhere.

00:52:32.430 --> 00:52:35.460 align:middle line:84%
So things are a
little slower, and I

00:52:35.460 --> 00:52:37.110 align:middle line:90%
appreciate that very much.

00:52:37.110 --> 00:52:46.020 align:middle line:90%


00:52:46.020 --> 00:52:48.230 align:middle line:84%
I think the creative
process eases.

00:52:48.230 --> 00:52:50.840 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of
overlapping where

00:52:50.840 --> 00:52:54.140 align:middle line:84%
you can take a lot of
those skills, knowledge.

00:52:54.140 --> 00:52:59.120 align:middle line:84%
I mean, for instance, for me
to be able to paint a boat,

00:52:59.120 --> 00:53:02.690 align:middle line:84%
because I've worked
on boats for so long,

00:53:02.690 --> 00:53:07.150 align:middle line:84%
I can actually see and make
sure that it looks correct.

00:53:07.150 --> 00:53:10.360 align:middle line:84%
Because if the lines
are off, the shape

00:53:10.360 --> 00:53:13.030 align:middle line:84%
is slightly distorted
for whatever reason,

00:53:13.030 --> 00:53:16.160 align:middle line:84%
it can be quite irritating
to a lot of people,

00:53:16.160 --> 00:53:18.458 align:middle line:84%
especially if they know how
boats are supposed to look.

00:53:18.458 --> 00:53:29.200 align:middle line:90%


00:53:29.200 --> 00:53:30.850 align:middle line:84%
>> When something
is made by hand,

00:53:30.850 --> 00:53:34.030 align:middle line:84%
it connects the maker with
the material, for one,

00:53:34.030 --> 00:53:39.310 align:middle line:84%
whether it's clay
or wood or silver.

00:53:39.310 --> 00:53:41.800 align:middle line:84%
There's an actual
physical connection

00:53:41.800 --> 00:53:45.710 align:middle line:84%
between the maker
and the material.

00:53:45.710 --> 00:53:49.290 align:middle line:90%
It also implies a uniqueness.

00:53:49.290 --> 00:53:53.645 align:middle line:84%
The item that's made,
it's not mass produced.

00:53:53.645 --> 00:53:55.180 align:middle line:90%
It's a one-off.

00:53:55.180 --> 00:53:59.500 align:middle line:84%
Even if it's made in a
mold or to a pattern,

00:53:59.500 --> 00:54:01.810 align:middle line:84%
each handmade item is
going to be unique.

00:54:01.810 --> 00:54:05.500 align:middle line:84%
It's going to have the
actual mark of the maker

00:54:05.500 --> 00:54:07.880 align:middle line:84%
on it, because their
hands have touched it.

00:54:07.880 --> 00:54:11.910 align:middle line:90%


00:54:11.910 --> 00:54:15.263 align:middle line:84%
The value of artisan
work in a community,

00:54:15.263 --> 00:54:16.680 align:middle line:84%
particularly in a
small community,

00:54:16.680 --> 00:54:18.150 align:middle line:84%
it connects people
to each other.

00:54:18.150 --> 00:54:20.400 align:middle line:10%
When I go see a
potter or a jeweler

00:54:20.400 --> 00:54:23.340 align:middle line:10%
and I take a bowl or a
cup from that potter,

00:54:23.340 --> 00:54:25.770 align:middle line:10%
